<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="165" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">
Total body length ranged from 11-15 mm. Hooks 6-8. Anterior teeth 11-15 and posterior teeth 15-35, respectively. Rigid and opaque body (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. A Zonosagitta nagae (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704206" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">22A</figureCitation>
). Long and dense teeth. Collarette present on neck (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. A Zonosagitta nagae (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704206" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">22B</figureCitation>
). Intestinal diverticula absent (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Intestinal diverticular (shown by white arrow) A Aidanosagitta regularis (present) B Ferosagitta robusta (present) C Zonosagitta nagae (absent) D Zonosagitta bedoti (absent)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704191" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">7C</figureCitation>
). Eyes 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“D”">&quot;D&quot;</normalizedToken>
-shaped with 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“E”">&quot;E&quot;</normalizedToken>
-shaped eye pigments (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. A Zonosagitta nagae (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704206" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">22B</figureCitation>
). Anterior fins 27.7% of body length and 1.5 times longer than posterior fins. Anterior fins beginning in front of ventral ganglion and partially rayed. Starting points of anterior fins 28.6% and ending points of anterior fins 59.8% of body length, respectively (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. A Zonosagitta nagae (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704206" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">22A, D</figureCitation>
). Posterior fins 18.0% of body length. Starting points of posterior fins 67.8% and ending points of posterior fins 91.9% of body length, respectively. Posterior fins connecting with anterior fins partially rayed (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. A Zonosagitta nagae (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704206" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">22A, E</figureCitation>
). Seminal vesicles conical-shaped with small indentations and well separated from posterior fins (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. A Zonosagitta nagae (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704206" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">22C</figureCitation>
). Eggs reached posterior of anterior fins. Corona ciliata beginning behind eyes and elongated over neck (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. A Zonosagitta nagae (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704206" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">22C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
